Privacy Policy

1. Introduction
Jam ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share your data when you use our app.

2. Information We Collect
Account Information: Email and password when signing up.
Google Authentication Data: If you sign in with Google, we receive basic profile information.
User-Generated Content: Posts, comments, and other content you share.
Usage Data: Interaction data to improve app functionality.
3. How We Use Your Information
To create and manage your account.
To provide app features and improve user experience.
To send verification emails and necessary notifications.
4. Sharing Your Information
We do not sell or share your data with third parties, except:

When required by law.
To integrate third-party authentication services like Google Sign-In.
5. Security
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data. However, no online service is completely secure.

6. Your Rights
You can update or delete your account anytime.
You can contact us for any privacy-related requests.
7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Please review it periodically.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions, contact us at: [Your Contact Email].
